Description: Body fragment of a pottery closed vessel; on outside, cream slip, brown/black narrow horizontal strip; wide arch below framing three concentric circles. Hard, coarse, reddish clay, Munsell 2.5YR 6/6 (light red), with numerous dark and white inclusions.
Bibliographic references: Weber 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus anderen ägyptischen Fundorten (TD 317)
Acquisition notes: Found unregistered in the Department in 2010, in a box with other sherds from Tell Dafana.
